message.content: cs.IT, cs.IT is the most likely category as the paper deals with information theory and communication systems. Other possible categories could be cs.DS (discrete mathematics) as the paper uses techniques from additive combinatorics, cs.MS (mathematical physics) as the paper uses results from fractal geometry, cs.NA (numerical analysis) as the paper discusses numerical evaluations, and cs.CC (computational complexity) as the paper discusses the hardness of finding the exact number of DoF in ICs with rational channel coefficients.
